headline.main: FIERCE FIGHT RAGES FOR TRIESTE'S PORT; Yugoslav Partisans and Foe Locked in Artillery Duel for Adriatic City TOWN REPORTED IN RUINS Guerrillas Seen Regaining the Initiative Near Spalato -- Enemy Executes 300

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Oct. 1 (U.P.) -- The Yugoslav People's Army of Liberation reported tonight that heavily reinforced German troops and Yugoslav guerrillas were locked in heavy artillery duels for possession of the industrial port of Fiume and the smaller city of Gorizia in northeastern Italy.
